---
import GuideLayout from "../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro";

const title = "Parameter Store cost optimization (reduce API calls safely)";
const description =
  "A high-leverage playbook to reduce SSM Parameter Store costs: cache parameters, reduce churn-driven fetches, and avoid per-request lookups. Includes validation steps and related tools.";
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What's the biggest lever for Parameter Store cost?",
    a: "Reduce API calls. Most spend is request-driven, especially from repeated GetParameter calls in hot paths or during churn events.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I reduce calls without risking stale config?",
    a: "Cache with a reasonable TTL, reload on deploy, and implement a safe refresh mechanism. Avoid fetching on every request unless strictly necessary.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why do costs spike in Kubernetes and serverless?",
    a: "Pod churn and cold starts can trigger many fetches. If each instance fetches multiple parameters, request volume scales quickly.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do I validate the optimization?",
    a: "Track API calls/day before/after and confirm configuration refresh still works as expected (deploy reloads, TTL refresh, and rotation events).",
  },
];
---
<GuideLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/guides/aws-ssm-parameter-store-cost-optimization"
  lastUpdated="2026-01-22"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p class="muted">
    Parameter Store cost reduction is mostly about reducing GetParameter volume while keeping configuration handling safe
    and reliable.
  </p>

  <h2>1) Cache parameters</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Fetch parameters once per process startup and cache in memory.</li>
    <li>Add a TTL refresh for long-running services (minutes, not seconds).</li>
    <li>Batch with GetParameters where possible.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2) Avoid per-request lookups</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Do not call Parameter Store on every incoming request.</li>
    <li>Keep config in memory and reload via deploy or refresh loop.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3) Reduce churn-driven fetches</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Reduce pod churn and cold starts where possible.</li>
    <li>Fix retry loops that multiply fetches during incidents.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Validation checklist</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Measure API calls/day for a representative week, then compare after changes.</li>
    <li>Confirm refresh behavior: deploy reload, TTL refresh, and manual rotations.</li>
    <li>Confirm failure modes: if Parameter Store is throttled, do you degrade safely?</li>
  </ul>

